item.description:
This event open to all kayak types as well as canoes

We'll meet at Chapman's Landing off of Rt. 108 Stratham NH and paddle up the Squamscott River into downtown Exeter with the incoming tide. High Tide is approx. 1:30pm in Exeter. Bring a snack and water or other beverage as we'll stop at the town landing in Exeter and have a short picnic in the adjacent park.

Click photo above for a view of boat launch at Chapmans Landing

Life vests aka PFDs must be worn when paddling with this group

Directions:
* Follow Rte. 108 North from Stratham or South from Newmarket.
* Chapman's landing is well marked & next to the metal bridge over river.

Google Maps directions to Chapman's Landing Boat Launch
item.name: Squamscott River to Downtown Exeter Paddle
